#Text=OFF TO THE WOODS

#Text=WHETHER Danny Rugg was afraid the principal had seen him trying to force a fight on Bert , or whether the unexpected fall that came to him , caused it , no one knew , but certainly , for the next few days , Danny let Bert alone .
#Text=When he passed him he scowled , or shook his fist , or muttered something about " getting even , " but this was all .
#Text=Perhaps it was the thought of what Bert had seen fall from Danny 's pocket that made the bully less anxious to keep up the quarrel .
#Text=At any rate , Bert was left alone and he was glad of it .
#Text=He was not afraid , but he liked peace .
#Text=The school days went on , and the classes settled down to their work for the long Winter term .
#Text=And the thought of the snow and ice that would comparatively soon be with them , made the Bobbsey twins rejoice .
#Text=" Charley Mason and I are going to make a dandy big bob this year , " said Bert one day .
#Text=" It 's going to carry ten fellows . "
#Text=" And no girls ? " asked Nan with a smile .
#Text=She was walking along behind her brother , with Grace and Nellie .
#Text=" Sure , we 'll let you girls ride once in a while , " said Charley , as he caught up to his chum .
#Text=" But you ca n't steer . "
#Text=" I steered a bob once , " said Grace , who was quite athletic for her age .
#Text=" It was Danny Rugg 's , too . "
#Text=" Pooh !

#Text= And if you 'll come with me I 'll treat you all to some , " exclaimed Nellie Parks , whose father was quite well off .

column1: #Text=" I have some of my birthday money left . "
#Text=" Oh , but there are five of us ! " cried Nan , counting .
#Text=" That is too much -- twenty-five cents , Nellie . "
#Text=" I 've got fifty , and really it is very hot today . "
#Text=It was warm , being the end of September , with Indian Summer near at hand .
#Text=" Well , let 's go to Johnson 's , " suggested Nellie .
#Text=" They have the best cream . "
#Text=" Oh , here comes Flossie and Freddie ! " exclaimed Nan .
#Text=" We do n't want to take them , Nellie .

column3:
_	_	_	_

#Text= Of course I 'll take them ! " exclaimed Nellie , generously .

column1: #Text=" I 've got fifty cents , I told you . "
#Text=" I 'll give them each a penny and let them run along home , " offered Bert .
#Text=" No , I 'm going to treat them , too , " insisted Nellie .
#Text=" Come on ! " she called to the little twins , " we 're going to get ice cream cones , it 's so warm . "
#Text=" Oh , goodie ! " cried Flossie .
#Text=" I was just wishing for one . "
#Text=" So was I , " added her brother .
#Text=" And I 'll ask you to my party next week , " the little girl went on .
#Text=" I 'm going to have one on my birthday . "
#Text=" Oh , are you really , Flossie ? " asked Nan .
#Text=" I had n't heard about it . "
#Text=" Yep -- I am .

#Text= And it 's half my party , ' cause my birthday 's the same day , " explained Freddie .

column1: #Text=" So you can come to my party at the same time , Nellie . "
#Text=" Thank you , dear , I shall .

#Text= Hey , Charley , " called Danny , " come here , I want to speak to you . "

column1: #Text=" I 'm busy now , " answered Charley .
#Text=" Bert and I have something to do . "
#Text=" So have I. I 've got a dandy plan . "
#Text=" Well , I 'll see you later , " spoke Charley .
#Text=He had once been quite friendly with Danny , but he grew not to like his ways , and so became more chummy with Bert , who was very glad , for he liked Charley .
#Text=The two boys went on to Bert 's barn , where they were going to build the bob sled .
#Text=The girls , with Flossie and Freddie , went on the Bobbsey lawn , where there were some easy chairs .
#Text=They sat in the shade of the trees , and Freddie had Snap do some of his tricks for the visitors .
#Text=" Can he jump through a hoop , covered with paper as they do in the circus ? " asked Nellie .
#Text=" Oh , we never thought to try that , " said Freddie .
#Text=" I 'm going to make one , " and , filled with this new idea , he hurried into the house .
#Text=" Dinah , " he said , " I want some paper and paste . "
